headline: International Business Machines (NYSE:IBM) Expands Semiconductor Research With Tokyo Electron Partnership
summary: International Business Machines (NYSE:IBM) recently announced the extension of its strategic partnership with Tokyo Electron (TEL), focusing on developing technologies essential for generative AI. This could have enhanced market confidence, driving a 14% increase in its stock price over the last quarter. During this period, IBM declared a stable $1.67 quarterly dividend and introduced AI-driven projects like the Granite 3.2 LLM, which align with market trends favoring AI innovations. Despite...

headline: Tokyo Electron and IBM Renew Collaboration for Advanced Semiconductor Technology
summary: Today, IBM and Tokyo Electron (TEL) announced an extension of their agreement for the joint research and development of advanced semiconductor technologies. The new 5-year agreement will focus on the continued advancement of technology for next-generation semiconductor nodes and architectures to power the age of generative AI.
